<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-335-110  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 335 110.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  June 5 1989 v35 n1761 p33(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hear AIL Systems expects B-1B bomber add-on from AF. (Eaton AILSystems; Air Force)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The long-delayed $500 million contract to upgrade the B-1Bbomber's electronic countermeasures defensive avionics system mayfinally be granted to Eaton AIL Systems during the summer of 1989.andO;The latest system designed by AIL was being reviewed by the AirForce during Jun 1989, and if approved the contract will begranted and full progress payments, withheld from AIL since 1988,could also be resumed.andP;  The government funding might reviveRockwell International's interest in acquiring AIL, and the fullprogress payments would be additional incentive.andP;  A new singlefrequency coder prevents the radar warning subsystem from becomingoverloaded by picking out and tracking the most serious threats,and a tail warning defensive system is now undergoing flighttests.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Eaton Corp. AIL Div. (contracts)Rockwell International Corp. (planning).andO;Ticker:    ROK.andO;Topic:     Defense ContractsGovernment FundingAcquisitionUnited States. Air ForceB-1B (Bomber).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>